{
  "texts": [
    "In many contexts the interventions delivered may not be aligned with best evidence leading to unwarranted care variation and potential harm.",
    "Further, interventions may not be aligned with the values, preferences and acceptability attitudes among care recipients (and/or their carers), substantiating the need for global guidelines in this area [21].",
    "Importantly, values and preferences of older people likely differ to younger adults.",
    "From the perspective of healthy ageing, carers are an essential workforce for supporting functional ability in older people and enabling ageing in place.",
    "The perspectives of carers are therefore critical to ensure care planning and delivery for any health condition experienced by an older people is feasible and acceptable and does not negatively impact on the quality of life of the carer [22,23]."
  ]
}